Date: Tue, 12 Jul 2022 16:21:32 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] drm/i915/gt: Serialize GRDOM access between multiple engine resets
Mime-version: 1.0
Content-type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-transfer-encoding: 8bit
Git-commit: b24dcf1dc507f69ed3b5c66c2b6a0209ae80d4d4
Patch-mainline: v5.19-rc7
Alt-commit: 336561a914fc0c6f1218228718f633b31b7af1c3
References: git-fixes

Don't allow two engines to be reset in parallel, as they would both
try to select a reset bit (and send requests to common registers)
and wait on that register, at the same time. Serialize control of
the reset requests/acks using the uncore->lock, which will also ensure
that no other GT state changes at the same time as the actual reset.

